ARRAY

class Solution {
    public int removeDuplicates(int[] nums) {

        int i = 0; // points to last unique element

        for (int j = 1; j < nums.length; j++) {

            // if new unique element found
            if (nums[j] != nums[i]) {
                i++;                 // move pointer
                nums[i] = nums[j];   // place new element
            }
        }

        return i + 1; // total unique elements
    }
}

use 2 pointers:

i → last unique element position
j → current element (scanner)

Time Complexity: O(n)
